First Lady Melania Trump and Mrs. Lorena Castillo de Varela of Panama had lunch at the White House and discussed various topics, including their initiatives in their respective governments. Mrs. Varela talked about her involvement in the Red Cross and as the UNAIDS Special Ambassador for AIDS in Latin America, as well as her efforts in the autism community. The two also discussed the connection between media and politics in the US and Panama. Mrs. Trump shared her intentions for her role as First Lady in the coming months.